364
00:30:34,560 --> 00:30:35,993
It's good
to see you again, Riley.

365
00:30:40,632 --> 00:30:43,726
[phone ringing]

366
00:30:43,802 --> 00:30:45,497
I think we woke up
your package.

367
00:30:50,342 --> 00:30:54,210
<i>(Man) Riley.</i>
<i>Can you change a tap?</i>

368
00:30:54,279 --> 00:30:55,246
Two beers.

369
00:30:55,314 --> 00:30:56,178
Be right back.

370
00:31:05,190 --> 00:31:06,452
Hello?

371
00:31:06,525 --> 00:31:10,120
<i>Hello, Will Montgomery.</i>

372
00:31:10,195 --> 00:31:12,356
<i>[coughing]</i>

373
00:31:14,466 --> 00:31:16,127
Who is this?

374
00:31:16,201 --> 00:31:19,466
<i>You don't recognize</i>
<i>my voice, Gum?</i>

375
00:31:19,538 --> 00:31:23,030
- <i>I wanted to be there for you</i>
<i>at the prison.</i> - Vincent?

376
00:31:23,108 --> 00:31:24,939
<i>Give you a welcome</i>
<i>when you got out.</i>

377
00:31:25,010 --> 00:31:28,241
<i>But you know how it is,</i>
<i>time just slipped away.</i>

378
00:31:28,313 --> 00:31:30,281
Well, hallelujah, man.
You're alive.

379
00:31:30,349 --> 00:31:34,786
Shit. You know what? Everybody's
telling me you're dead.

380
00:31:34,853 --> 00:31:38,653
<i>I suppose that depends on your</i>
<i>interpretation of the word "dead."</i>

381
00:31:38,724 --> 00:31:43,252
<i>'Cause I'm certainly not living.</i>
<i>[coughing]</i>

382
00:31:43,328 --> 00:31:46,661
