00:59:02,366 --> 00:59:03,993
It's all yours, brother.

739
00:59:06,737 --> 00:59:08,932
<i>(Lefleur)</i>
<i>Five-kilo-two-zero.</i>

740
00:59:09,006 --> 00:59:14,205
- Again, that's 5K20.
- Thanks, pal.

741
00:59:14,278 --> 00:59:18,442
Looky here, did you just turn
white on me all of a sudden?

742
00:59:18,515 --> 00:59:19,641
Who dat is?

743
01:00:11,935 --> 01:00:14,529
Remember where
we dropped off Montgomery?

744
01:00:14,605 --> 01:00:16,163
His daughter's address?

745
01:00:16,239 --> 01:00:18,036
Yes,
Coronado and something.

746
01:00:18,108 --> 01:00:20,838
- Prentiss.
- Hey, boss?

747
01:00:20,911 --> 01:00:22,640
A guy matching
Montgomery's description

748
01:00:22,713 --> 01:00:25,147
just jacked a cab
five blocks from here.

749
01:00:25,215 --> 01:00:27,183
Get this, the cabbie said
he was sweating him

750
01:00:27,250 --> 01:00:29,218
about a guy missing
a leg and his fingers.

751
01:00:29,286 --> 01:00:32,778
They're tracking the stolen
cab back into the Quarter.

752
01:02:02,045 --> 01:02:03,637
- Don't hurt me, man!
- Whose cab is this?

753
01:02:03,714 --> 01:02:05,682
It's mine.

754
01:02:05,749 --> 01:02:07,376
But that ain't my number.

755
01:02:08,819 --> 01:02:09,808
Open the trunk.

756
01:02:12,022 --> 01:02:13,546
There he is. We got him.

757
01:02:16,226 --> 01:02:18,387
Whoa.
That's somebody else's GPS.

758
01:02:20,864 --> 01:02:22,957
Montgomery! Get your God
damn knees on the ground.

759
01:02:23,033 --> 01:02:26,434
Will Montgomery, you are under
arrest for violation of parole,

760
01:02:26,503 --> 01:02:29,131
illegally accessing
confidential FBI records,

761
01:02:29,206 --> 01:02:33,006
<i>assaulting a federal agent,</i>
<i>and resisting arrest.</i>

762
01:02:33,076 --> 01:02:35,977
- We're bringing him back now.
- You've gotta listen to me.

763
01:02:36,046 --> 01:02:38,412
- No we don't.
- He's gonna kill her.

764
01:02:38,482 --> 01:02:40,109
<i>(Tessler)</i>
<i>Oh, it's a neat story.</i>

765
01:02:40,183 --> 01:02:42,174
Vincent Kinsey has
come back from the dead?

766
01:02:42,252 --> 01:02:43,378
<i>(Matthews)</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

767
01:02:45,522 --> 01:02:46,989
Me, if I were
coming back from the dead,

768
01:02:47,057 --> 01:02:48,991
it wouldn't be
for daughter killing.

769
01:02:49,059 --> 01:02:51,653
It'd be to go to Rick's Cabaret
to see some naked ladies.

770
01:02:51,728 --> 01:02:53,855
(phone ringing)

771
01:02:53,930 --> 01:02:56,831
- I gotta take that.
- Ah, you want me to take a message?

772
01:02:56,900 --> 01:03:00,028
- I've only got eight rings to
pick up that call. - Hey, sit back.

773
01:03:00,103 --> 01:03:04,631
(phone ringing)

774
01:03:04,708 --> 01:03:05,732
(bones breaking)

775
01:03:34,304 --> 01:03:36,534
(phone ringing)

776
01:03:40,277 --> 01:03:42,575
Hello?

777
01:03:42,646 --> 01:03:44,807
Hi, I'm here.
I'm here.

778
01:03:49,152 --> 01:03:50,346
(resetting bone)

779
01:03:50,420 --> 01:03:52,354
I'm here.

780
01:03:52,422 --> 01:03:55,220
Really coming down to the
wire on this one, eh, Gum?

781
01:03:55,292 --> 01:03:58,523
Have trouble getting it
out of your pocket?

782
01:03:58,595 --> 01:04:01,428
I'm not.
I just, I just...

783
01:04:01,498 --> 01:04:02,931
Sounds like
you're out of breath.

784
01:04:02,999 --> 01:04:04,728
Tell me something, Gum.

785
01:04:04,801 --> 01:04:07,269
What's the scenery like
down there in Tuscaloosa?

786
01:04:07,337 --> 01:04:09,328
<i>I always wanted</i>
<i>to take that ride along the Gulf.</i>

787
01:04:09,406 --> 01:04:11,271
I don't have it.

788
01:04:11,341 --> 01:04:13,241
Or better yet, why don't
you tell me how Hoyt's doing,

789
01:04:13,310 --> 01:04:15,073
<i>seeing as that's</i>
<i>where you were anyway?</i>

790
01:04:15,145 --> 01:04:17,773
I don't have the money.

791
01:04:17,848 --> 01:04:19,577
What did I say to you
about lying to me?

792
01:04:19,649 --> 01:04:22,618
I'm sorry,
I just, I just...

793
01:04:22,686 --> 01:04:27,623
- Your daughter's dead.
- No, wait! Wait!

794
01:04:27,691 --> 01:04:30,888
You really
don't have it, do you?

795
01:04:30,961 --> 01:04:33,452
- I'll get you the money.
- <i>(Vincent) Good.</i>

796
01:04:33,530 --> 01:04:34,861
May I ask how?

797
01:04:39,336 --> 01:04:41,361
By going back to wrong.

798
01:04:50,814 --> 01:04:52,782
He got away on foot.
He went down the alley, okay?

799
01:04:52,849 --> 01:04:54,441
We gotta
set up a perimeter.

800
01:04:54,517 --> 01:04:56,485
Let's move.
Clear out!

801
01:05:33,757 --> 01:05:35,884
(phone ringing)

802
01:05:41,865 --> 01:05:42,695
Hello?

803
01:06:35,452 --> 01:06:37,079
What's going on?

804
01:06:37,153 --> 01:06:39,018
- Why are the feds after you?
- There's no time.

805
01:06:39,089 --> 01:06:41,387
- Vincent's alive.
- What? What are you talking about?

806
01:06:41,458 --> 01:06:45,724
He wants $10 million. He wants it
in three hours, and he has Alison.

807
01:06:45,795 --> 01:06:46,591
Oh, my God.

808
01:06:48,565 --> 01:06:50,089
The bank
we robbed that night,

809
01:06:50,166 --> 01:06:52,066
there was something else
in the vault.

810
01:06:52,135 --> 01:06:54,933
A gold reserve, there must've
been 100 million, easy.

811
01:06:55,005 --> 01:06:56,768
There's no way
you can walk in there

812
01:06:56,840 --> 01:06:59,570
and steal $10 million
worth of gold bricks

813
01:06:59,642 --> 01:07:01,109
in the middle
of a business day.

814
01:07:01,177 --> 01:07:03,737
But that's why
I need your help.

815
01:07:03,813 --> 01:07:05,838
I already told you,
this isn't my life anymore.

816
01:07:05,915 --> 01:07:08,782
- I know. I know.
- It's not yours either.

817
01:07:08,852 --> 01:07:12,049
He's going to kill her.

818
01:07:12,122 --> 01:07:15,114
I, I can hear it
in his voice.

819
01:07:15,191 --> 01:07:18,422
He's not the same person.

820
01:07:20,030 --> 01:07:22,294
He's going to kill
my little girl.

821
01:07:28,538 --> 01:07:29,903
Okay.

822
01:07:29,973 --> 01:07:31,201
Okay.

823
01:07:34,944 --> 01:07:36,935
(sirens)

824
01:07:42,719 --> 01:07:44,186
Oh, man.

825
01:07:49,726 --> 01:07:53,321
- You LeFleur?
- Yes sir, I am. LeFleur, yes sir.

826
01:07:53,396 --> 01:07:56,126
A guy jacked your cab a little while
ago. He was looking for someone?

827
01:07:56,199 --> 01:07:59,635
Well, he was looking for
that mope, Jimmy Morgan, sir.

828
01:07:59,702 --> 01:08:01,670
Be a peach and show me
his hack license, will you?

829
01:08:01,738 --> 01:08:03,933
Yes, yes, officer, sir.

830
01:08:04,007 --> 01:08:05,838
I'll look it up
for you, inspector.

831
01:08:05,909 --> 01:08:07,774
<i>He been with us</i>
<i>two years.</i>

832
01:08:07,844 --> 01:08:10,005
Never any problem.

833
01:08:10,080 --> 01:08:12,776
Although he do
scare my kids

834
01:08:12,849 --> 01:08:16,478
when they come to visit
their daddy at work.

835
01:08:16,553 --> 01:08:18,350
My kids
are in their 20s.

836
01:08:23,093 --> 01:08:24,424
Vincent Kinsey.

837
01:08:26,729 --> 01:08:27,923
Much obliged.

838
01:08:29,265 --> 01:08:30,197
Let's go.

839
01:08:37,607 --> 01:08:39,598
(sirens)

840
01:08:44,447 --> 01:08:47,382
Fat Tuesday,
everybody go crazy.

841
01:09:25,655 --> 01:09:28,249
We're six blocks away from
the bank, you do realize that.

842
01:09:28,324 --> 01:09:30,155
- Have a little faith.
- Okay.

843
01:09:33,429 --> 01:09:36,159
(Will) I've considered doing
this for the last 8 years.

844
01:10:15,205 --> 01:10:17,503
(Will) Thirty meters, then we go left.

845
01:11:26,776 --> 01:11:30,507
Montgomery doesn't have the
money, but he needs the money,

846
01:11:30,580 --> 01:11:32,980
which means he's only got
one play left to make.

847
01:11:33,049 --> 01:11:37,213
Get me a list of every bank that he's
stepped into in the city of New Orleans.

848
01:11:37,287 --> 01:11:40,017
My guess is one of them
he's going to step into again.

849
01:11:52,302 --> 01:11:53,098
We're through.

850
01:11:55,305 --> 01:11:57,603
- Five minutes till the alarm.
- Think that'll be enough?

851
01:12:06,716 --> 01:12:07,944
<i>(Will)</i>
<i>Here it comes.</i>

852
01:12:52,662 --> 01:12:54,960
(alarm buzzing)

853
01:12:55,031 --> 01:12:57,795
Fire alarm just went off
at Parish Community Bank.

854
01:12:57,867 --> 01:13:00,199
<i>(Harland) That's him.</i>
<i>Get us there now!</i>

855
01:13:06,576 --> 01:13:08,237
<i>(Firefighter)</i>
<i>Let's go, boys.</i>

856
01:13:26,796 --> 01:13:28,821
The alarm will have
triggered by now. We gotta go.

857
01:13:28,898 --> 01:13:31,128
I just want to see if I can get
a little more gold out of it.

858
01:13:35,004 --> 01:13:38,405
Come on, guys, let's go!
Go, go, go!

859
01:14:06,502 --> 01:14:07,867
Could you please
hurry up, sir?

860
01:14:07,937 --> 01:14:08,767
(vault beeping)

861
01:14:10,606 --> 01:14:12,437
Come on, Will,
we gotta go.

862
01:14:14,877 --> 01:14:16,276
Come on!

863
01:14:28,257 --> 01:14:29,121
Huh.

864
01:14:31,527 --> 01:14:33,188
<i>(Harland)</i>
<i>Well, what do you know.</i>

865
01:15:16,072 --> 01:15:18,939
So, you worked all this out from prison?

866
01:15:19,008 --> 01:15:20,600
I was bored.

867
01:15:24,180 --> 01:15:26,114
Boss, hey. Listen to this. Say again.

868
01:15:26,182 --> 01:15:28,776
<i>We have the two suspects.</i>
<i>They're in Rileys truck</i>

869
01:15:28,851 --> 01:15:30,546
<i>on North Reters</i>
<i>headin' towards the ferry.</i>

870
01:15:30,620 --> 01:15:32,520
Do not take them
until they're off the ferry.

871
01:15:32,588 --> 01:15:35,455
I repeat, do not take them
until they're off the ferry.

872
01:15:35,525 --> 01:15:37,959
We take them now.
We got 'em boxed in.

873
01:15:38,027 --> 01:15:40,359
<i>(Harland) You don't corner a weasel</i>
<i>unless you wanna get bit.</i>

874
01:15:40,429 --> 01:15:42,590
I hope you know what you're
doing. Takes eight minutes

875
01:15:42,665 --> 01:15:45,463
...to get across the river on that ferry.
- Wait for strength in numbers.

876
01:15:45,535 --> 01:15:47,901
And when we get Montgomery,
he'll be as red-handed

877
01:15:47,970 --> 01:15:52,737
as the boy who put his palm on the
gas stove to see how hot it really was.

878
01:15:52,808 --> 01:15:53,797
Okay.

879
01:16:00,983 --> 01:16:04,817
Don't make a move until all
four wheels touch Louisiana soil.

880
01:16:04,887 --> 01:16:06,081
<i>(Agent)</i>
<i>Copy that.</i>

881
01:16:34,750 --> 01:16:36,012
Hands in the air.

882
01:16:36,085 --> 01:16:37,245
Hands in the air now!

883
01:16:40,523 --> 01:16:43,083
Happy Fat Tuesday, officer.

884
01:17:39,115 --> 01:17:41,208
Come on.
Come on.

885
01:17:41,283 --> 01:17:44,411
Come on, get out.
Get out!

886
01:17:44,487 --> 01:17:47,251
(phone ringing)

887
01:17:47,323 --> 01:17:49,052
<i>(Vincent)</i>
<i>Time is up, buddy.</i>

888
01:17:49,125 --> 01:17:50,183
I've got it.

889
01:17:50,259 --> 01:17:53,558
Ah, I am impressed.

890
01:17:53,629 --> 01:17:56,063
You listen to a little
Creedence before you went in?

891
01:17:56,132 --> 01:18:02,037
No, I didn't listen to CCR. That didn't
work out so well the last time, did it?

892
01:18:02,104 --> 01:18:03,628
I missed you, old buddy.

893
01:18:03,706 --> 01:18:05,503
I want to talk to her.

894
01:18:05,574 --> 01:18:07,542
No, you'll talk to her
when you give me the money.

895
01:18:07,610 --> 01:18:09,237
I wanna talk
to my daughter now!

896
01:18:09,311 --> 01:18:12,075
<i>I wanna hear her voice now!</i>

897
01:18:12,148 --> 01:18:13,615
It's your father.

898
01:18:13,683 --> 01:18:15,583
- Hello?
- Alison.

899
01:18:15,651 --> 01:18:17,448
Alison, did he hurt you?

900
01:18:17,520 --> 01:18:20,580
No, but he scares me.

901
01:18:20,656 --> 01:18:22,886
I'm gonna be there soon.
I'm gonna get you outta this.

902
01:18:22,958 --> 01:18:25,392
<i>(Will)</i>
<i>This is my fault.</i>

903
01:18:25,461 --> 01:18:29,454
Get my money
to the fairgrounds now.

904
01:18:43,679 --> 01:18:45,806
Sorry, boss.

905
01:18:45,881 --> 01:18:49,817
Finally starting to recognize the
skills of Will Montgomery, huh?

906
01:18:49,885 --> 01:18:51,978
You got those listings
from the cab dispatcher?

907
01:18:52,054 --> 01:18:54,488
GPS breakdowns?
Yeah, why?

908
01:18:54,557 --> 01:18:56,582
I told you Kinsey
ditched his GPS

909
01:18:56,659 --> 01:18:58,650
in the back of a cab
in the French Quarter.

910
01:18:58,728 --> 01:19:01,253
I'm not interested in today's.
I wanna see the last few weeks.

911
01:19:01,330 --> 01:19:03,389
Kinsey's gonna get the
money from Montgomery,

912
01:19:03,466 --> 01:19:06,026
then he's gonna have to have
some kind of neutral rendezvous.

913
01:19:06,102 --> 01:19:08,502
And if that's the case,
he's been casing it for weeks.

914
01:19:08,571 --> 01:19:10,801
Uptown, Lakefront,
Beauvoir, Gretna,

915
01:19:10,873 --> 01:19:12,636
- West Bank.
- Beauvoir?

916
01:19:12,708 --> 01:19:15,802
- Is that the fairground?
- Yeah, I think so.

917
01:19:15,878 --> 01:19:17,937
Twenty minutes
from out of town?

918
01:19:18,013 --> 01:19:20,447
- That doesn't sound like a cab ride to me.
- Nicely done, boss.

919
01:19:20,516 --> 01:19:21,983
We might actually
catch this prick.

920
01:20:00,022 --> 01:20:01,387
Where's Alison?

921
01:20:06,395 --> 01:20:08,090
In the trunk?

922
01:20:10,299 --> 01:20:14,201
You look good, Will.
The same.

923
01:20:14,270 --> 01:20:16,704
Where is she?

924
01:20:16,772 --> 01:20:18,603
She's safe.

925
01:20:40,329 --> 01:20:42,559
The money.
Hand her over.

926
01:20:45,167 --> 01:20:47,158
I said, hand her over!

927
01:20:48,671 --> 01:20:50,730
You got the money.
You win.

928
01:20:50,806 --> 01:20:52,137
Vincent!

929
01:20:52,208 --> 01:20:54,233
Over a janitor.

930
01:20:54,310 --> 01:21:01,079
You piss away 14 years of
friendship over an old man janitor?

931
01:21:01,150 --> 01:21:03,744
We're not killers.

932
01:21:03,819 --> 01:21:05,616
Well, maybe not then.

933
01:21:05,688 --> 01:21:10,250
None of this has anything
to do with my daughter.

934
01:21:10,326 --> 01:21:12,089
But it does, Will.

935
01:21:12,161 --> 01:21:14,629
Because you truly
love Alison.

936
01:21:14,697 --> 01:21:18,565
And in that single act
of betrayal eight years ago,

937
01:21:18,634 --> 01:21:24,300
you destroyed the only
thing I ever truly loved.

938
01:21:26,809 --> 01:21:28,037
Me.

939
01:21:34,717 --> 01:21:36,207
No! No!

940
01:21:39,555 --> 01:21:40,613
Daddy!

941
01:21:42,524 --> 01:21:45,391
[Alison calling
from trunk]

942
01:21:49,064 --> 01:21:50,292
<i>(Alison)</i>
<i>No!</i>

943
01:21:50,366 --> 01:21:51,526
Get me outta here!

944
01:21:56,572 --> 01:21:59,166
<i>(Alison)</i>
<i>Help!</i>

945
01:21:59,241 --> 01:22:00,367
Help!

946
01:22:03,879 --> 01:22:05,904
<i>Daddy,</i>
<i>get me outta here!</i>

947
01:22:12,221 --> 01:22:13,188
Help!

948
01:22:14,924 --> 01:22:17,893
(screaming)

949
01:23:16,986 --> 01:23:18,681
[screams]

950
01:23:19,655 --> 01:23:20,952
[whimpers]

951
01:23:29,965 --> 01:23:31,489
[screams]

952
01:23:39,174 --> 01:23:48,173
[choking, fighting,
yelling, groaning]

953
01:24:15,978 --> 01:24:17,468
[yells]

954
01:24:25,354 --> 01:24:27,686
[Alison coughing]
I've gotcha.

955
01:24:36,498 --> 01:24:38,966
[yells]

956
01:24:39,034 --> 01:24:41,832
[screams in agony]

957
01:25:07,162 --> 01:25:08,891
Oh, my God,
you're bleeding.

958
01:25:13,735 --> 01:25:15,498
I don't know what to do.

959
01:25:15,571 --> 01:25:16,401
What do I do?

960
01:25:20,109 --> 01:25:23,203
No, no, no.
Don't die.

961
01:25:23,278 --> 01:25:24,768
Don't die.

962
01:25:28,617 --> 01:25:31,177
Somebody help us!

963
01:25:31,253 --> 01:25:34,450
No, no, no.
You can't die.

964
01:25:34,523 --> 01:25:36,013
[groaning]

965
01:25:36,091 --> 01:25:37,956
Just stay with me.

966
01:25:41,964 --> 01:25:44,194
They're coming.
They're coming.

967
01:25:44,266 --> 01:25:49,499
Just hang in there.
Over here! Over here!

968
01:25:49,571 --> 01:25:52,301
(Harland)
There.

969
01:25:54,309 --> 01:25:55,799
You're gonna be okay.

970
01:26:13,662 --> 01:26:15,425
Oh, Jesus.

971
01:26:15,497 --> 01:26:18,227
No, no, no. He can't die.
You've gotta save him.

972
01:26:18,300 --> 01:26:20,996
Come on, let's
get him outta here.

973
01:26:27,109 --> 01:26:28,770
[yells in pain]

974
01:26:37,686 --> 01:26:39,210
Are you gonna
send him back to jail?

975
01:26:39,288 --> 01:26:41,017
Now, why would I do that?

976
01:26:41,089 --> 01:26:42,920
I'm sure that Vincent
Kinsey stole that gold.

977
01:26:42,991 --> 01:26:43,582
Take her up.

978
01:26:47,996 --> 01:26:49,793
Alison.

979
01:26:49,865 --> 01:26:51,355
I'm here, Dad.

980
01:27:50,926 --> 01:27:53,793
<i>HI, Dad.</i>
